<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-01-29T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-01-29T17:00:00-05:00" n="1621" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1621">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 811.0144/9.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Chargé <persName type="to">O’Shaughnessy</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-01-29T17:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 29, 1914, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>632. Consul, Nuevo Laredo, reports that he considers General Quintana’s
                            reply to demand for release of Cantú to be a diplomatic refusal and that
                            he is informed that one of the Generals has stated it was not only
                            intended to hold Cantú, but to execute him.</p>
                        <p>Bring to the attention of the appropriate authorities with renewed demand
                            for release of Cantú and intimate that unless this demand is immediately
                            complied with, this Government will find it necessary to consider
                            drastic measures in the premises.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>